Business Brief -- Horizon Financial Services:
   Investor Group Nominates
   Two People for the Board
The group has proposed that no compensation be paid to any
Horizon officer, director or employee that is contingent on a
merger, acquisition or change of control of the company,
unless the compensation amounts are submitted to a
shareholder vote and approved by a majority of shareholders
present and voting on the issue.
   A spokesman for the investor group declined to comment on
the filing.